SIMPLE: high-minded
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: High-minded
<hw>High"-mind"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Proud; arrogant.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Be not <qex>high-minded</qex>, but fear.</q> <rj><qau>Rom. xi.
20.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having, or characterized by, honorable pride; of or
pertaining to elevated principles and feelings; magnanimous; -- opposed
to <xex>mean</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>High-minded</qex>, manly recognition of those truths.</q>
<rj><qau>A. Norton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>High-mindedness</ent>⟦br⟧
